{
  "slug": "last30days",
  "name": "Last 30 Days",
  "type": "plugin",
  "description": "Researches any topic from the last 30 days across Reddit, X, and the web, surfacing real community discussions with engagement metrics",
  "longDescription": "Plugin with a single `last30days` skill invoked via `/last30days`. Uses a Python backend (`last30days.py` + 17 library modules) to search Reddit via OpenAI's `web_search` tool and X/Twitter via xAI's `x_search` tool, with web search fallback. Supports `--days=N` (1–30), `--quick` (8–12 results), `--deep` (50–70 Reddit, 40–60 X), and `--include-web` flags. Requires optional `OPENAI_API_KEY` and `XAI_API_KEY` — degrades gracefully to web-only without them. Returns posts with upvotes, likes, and reposts.",
